    "plan_content": "## Plan Summary\n\nI explored the codebase thoroughly — reading IRC, Nostr, and Telegram extensions plus the Plugin SDK (`core.ts`, `runtime-store.ts`, `chat-meta.ts`, and more). Here's the full plan for **7 new files** in `extensions/pulseboard/`, no existing files touched:\n\n### Files to Create\n\n| File | What it does |\n|---|---|\n| `package.json` | `@openclaw/pulseboard`, `\"module\"`, `openclaw` block with channel id/label/selectionLabel/docsPath/blurb |\n| `openclaw.plugin.json` | `id: \"pulseboard\"`, `channels: [\"pulseboard\"]`, empty `configSchema` |\n| `src/types.ts` | `PulseBoardAccount`, `PulseBoardConfig`, `PulseBoardMessage` interfaces |\n| `src/runtime.ts` | `createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>` → exports `getPulseBoardRuntime`/`setPulseBoardRuntime` |\n| `src/channel.ts` | `createChatChannelPlugin` with `base` (config/setup/messaging/gateway) + `outbound` (direct, 4000 char, sendText stub) → exports `pulseBoardPlugin` |\n| `index.ts` | `defineChannelPluginEntry` with id/name/description/plugin/setRuntime |\n| `setup-entry.ts` | `defineSetupPluginEntry(pulseBoardPlugin)` |\n\n### One Notable Constraint\n\n`getChatChannelMeta(\"pulseboard\")` requires `\"pulseboard\"` to be in `CHAT_CHANNEL_ORDER` inside `src/channels/ids.ts` (a core file we cannot touch). The plan therefore builds the `meta` object **inline** in `channel.ts` with the required `label`, `docsPath`, and `blurb` values, while still importing `getChatChannelMeta` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core`. A production integration would additionally add `\"pulseboard\"` to `CHAT_CHANNEL_ORDER`.",
